did.abstract: Correspondence, memoranda, reports, notes, printed matter, photographs, and sound recordings relating to the 1967 congressional campaign of Paul McCloskey in California, McCloskey's 1972 Republican presidential primary campaign, the 1976 presidential campaign of Jimmy Carter (especially in California), American foreign policy during the presidential administration of Jimmy Carter, and United States relations with Sweden. Digital copies of select records also available at https://digitalcollections.hoover.org.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research. Digital copies of select records also available at https://digitalcollections.hoover.org.

The Hoover Institution Archives only allows access to copies of audiovisual items, computer media, and digital files. To listen to sound recordings or to view videos, films, or digital files during your visit, please contact the Archives at least two working days before your arrival. We will then advise you of the accessibility of the material you wish to see or hear. Please note that not all material is immediately accessible.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, memoranda, reports, notes, printed matter, photographs, and sound recordings relating to the 1967 congressional campaign of Paul McCloskey in California, McCloskey's 1972 Republican presidential primary campaign, the 1976 presidential campaign of Jimmy Carter (especially in California), American foreign policy during the presidential administration of Jimmy Carter, and United States relations with Sweden.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Biographical sketches, awards and honors, curriculum vitae, clippings, printed matter, press release, correspondence, personal financial records, travel information, family announcements, social invitations and miscellaneous records relating to the life of Rodney Kennedy-Minott, arranged alphabetically by physical form

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence, clippings, budget, donations, printed matter, press release, telegrams, memoranda, reports, map, schedules, magazines relating to the Congressional campaign of Pete McCloskey vs. Shirley Temple Black, 1967-1969, Presidential GOP nomination campaign of 1971-1972 and Presidential campaign, election, and inauguration of Jimmy Carter, 1974-1977, arranged chronologically by physical form. Includes a few letters neither from nor to Rodney Kennedy-Minott

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, memoranda, press release, clippings, printed matter, schedules relating to Rodney Kennedy-Minott's nomination, subsequent Senate hearings leading to his appointment and swearing-in as Ambassador to Sweden. Also includes his briefing, prior to his assumption of office, on the organization of the Embassy, office staff, staff at the Ambassador's residence, salary information for the staff and the Ambassador, travel regulations, freight allowances for the Ambassador and his family and general information about Sweden. Includes letters neither from nor to Rodney Kennedy-Minott

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Ambassador's credential ceremony, correspondence, memoranda, schedules, clippings, notes, printed matter, telegrams, newsletters relating to the years of Rodney Kennedy-Minott's service as Ambassador to Sweden. Also enclosed are numerous invitations to parties, concerts, art show, boat show, opera, religious services received by the Ambassador and his wife and the invitations sent out by them to various social gatherings at their residence, the Nobel Prize ceremonies and related protocol information, banquets and receptions given by the Ambassador and his wife to the Nobel Prize winning American scientists. Also includes State Department communications, documents relating to American foreign policy, remarks made by Rodney Kennedy-Minott about President Carter and printed matter regarding Carter administration in general, and Rodney Kennedy-Minott's resignation as Ambassador to Sweden. Correspondence in this series includes letters neither to nor from Rodney Kennedy-Minott
